All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AlertHelper
The AlertHelper class provides methods for displaying different types of alerts (error, warning, information) using JavaFX's Alert dialog.
Coordinate
The Coordinate class represents a pair of row and column indices for a cell in a Sudoku grid.
GameController
The GameController class is responsible for managing the gameplay logic of the Sudoku application.
GameView
The GameView class represents the main game screen for the Sudoku application.
HelpButtonAdapter
The HelpButtonAdapter class is responsible for handling the logic when the help button is clicked in the Sudoku game.
IAlert
Interface that defines methods for displaying different types of alerts (error, warning, information).
Main
Main class that launches the Sudoku application.
Path
Utility class that contains the paths to the various resources used in the Sudoku application.
StartController
The StartController class manages the behavior of the start view of the Sudoku application.
StartView
This class represents the "Start View" of the Sudoku game.
Sudoku
Represents a Sudoku game model.
TryAgainController
The TryAgainController handles the logic for the Try Again view, including displaying the game result (win/lose) and navigating the user to the start view or exiting the game.
TryAgainView
This class represents the "Try Again" view in the Sudoku game.
